Data source
Compile and merge data from:
1.  Businesses that have previously sold to New York City
2.  Businesses that are located in New York from the Simply Analytics database that are processors or wholesalers/distributors of beans, leafy greens, or beef
3.  Businesses that were interviewed as part of this project.
4.  Businesses that were part of a list of businesses that sell NY Grown and Certified products

Variable names and description
-   ny: Location (in NY or not) (0/1)
-   wholesaler_distributor: wholesale, transportation or distribution businesses (0/1)
-   primary_processor: primary processor (0/1)
-   secondary_processor: secondary processor (0/1)
-   aggregator_cleaner: aggregator/cleaner (0/1)
-   sold_to_NYC: Has the business sold to New York City (0/1)
-   mwbe: Minority or Women owned business (0/1)
-   lrfs_business: Works with local farms
-   outofstatebusiness: A key player in the institutional bean supply chain that is located outside of New York


We assume that any business that sells through the local supply chain (i.e., was interviewed by research team, sold to NYC previously, was part of the list of businesses that are NY Grown & Certified, or identified by research as a key out-of-state seller) should be included in the bean supply chain model. 